{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78a09e9d-a2b2-4a16-977e-2de96e04e2cf","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_PoonrL15khzxK2NNa4v4PV","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Answering MSTest upgrade question"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_WPNQtckt4sBR05veJongwB","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2071de56959c4425a25cdfefb695580e"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-2071de56959c4425a25cdfefb695580e."}],"interactionId":"946f797a-6cf8-4839-a6b4-8e7f0863891d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code change request.\n\nLet me think about what I know about this:\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4 or so, Microsoft began transitioning from the legacy VSTest platform to the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, both runners were supported, and VSTest was still the default or at least supported. \n \nIn version 4.x, Microsoft dropped VSTest support entirely and switched exclusively to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, which means vstest.console can no longer discover tests without the VSTest adapter assemblies that are no longer included. To work around this, users would need to either downgrade, explicitly opt back into VSTest support if that's available, or migrate to the new testing platform. need to either:\n1. Switch their CI to use `dotnet test` which now uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default, or use the new `dotnet exec` / direct executable approach\n2. Or explicitly add back VSTest compatibility by setting `<EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>` or adding the VSTest bridge/adapter package, or setting a property like `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`\n\nSo the core issue is that MSTest.Sdk 3.x shipped with VSTest adapter references built in, allowing `vstest.console` to discover tests, but MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped that support entirely and now only works with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The solution is either migrating to `dotnet test` (which has native support in .NET 9+) or re-enabling the VSTest adapter through a property like `<GenerateVSTestAdapter>true</GenerateVSTestAdapter>`. Let me check what's in the working directory to understand the specific setup.","outputTokens":687,"requestId":"4813:1B7094:6620E16:6E94D43:69FC01F2"},"id":"f33aef5e-3f4d-48c6-99c9-80700844cb5e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T03:07:48.282Z","parentId":"854082c5-6560-41e5-b7df-5a7bdb8b9244"}
